&lt;h1&gt;Process Engineer - NPI &amp;amp; Test Development&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;603 Manufacturing | Precision Cable &amp;amp; Electro-Mechanical Assembly&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;603 Manufacturing is seeking a highly organized, technically capable Process Engineer to join our New Product Introduction (NPI) team. This role is responsible for developing robust manufacturing processes, creating standardized production documentation, supporting new product introductions, and owning cable and wire harness electrical test development.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The successful candidate will become the primary owner of Cirris CH2 test programming and validation. Prior Cirris experience is beneficial but not required for candidates with strong process engineering and electrical test fundamentals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This position works closely with Engineering, Quality, Manufacturing, and customers supporting high-reliability aerospace, defense, and space programs.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the introduction of new cable assemblies, wire harnesses, and electro-mechanical assemblies into production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review engineering drawings, schematics, BOMs, and customer specifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop manufacturing processes that support repeatability, quality, and throughput.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in first-piece and prototype builds, documenting lessons learned and process improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify tooling, fixturing, and equipment requirements for new programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain manufacturing work instructions, visual aids, process documentation, and standardized templates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish process controls, inspection points, and quality checkpoints.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document first article builds, process validations, and manufacturing best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Electrical Test Development&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain electrical test procedures for cable and wire harness assemblies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and validate Cirris CH2 test programs based on engineering drawings, schematics, netlists, and customer requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support continuity, isolation, hipot, resistance, and component verification testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot test failures and support root cause investigations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain revision control of test programs and associated documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Standardize test development methodologies across product families.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Space, Aerospace &amp;amp; Defense Compliance&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support programs requiring IPC/WHMA-A-620 Class 3 workmanship standards and Space Addendum requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interpret customer flow-down requirements and special process requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop documentation supporting traceability, configuration control, and audit readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support First Article Inspections (FAI) and customer audits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure manufacturing and test processes meet customer quality and reliability expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Continuous Improvement&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive improvements in manufacturing efficiency, documentation quality, testing methods, and process controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reduce process variation and improve manufacturing repeatability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support corrective actions and continuous improvement initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Qualifications&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Required&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Associate&#39;s or Bachelor&#39;s degree in Engineering, Engineering Technology, Electronics Technology, or related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of manufacturing engineering, process engineering, test engineering, or NPI expe

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ICS is a manufacturer of custom cables, harnesses, electro-mechanical assemblies and industrial panels. We are a turn-key supplier that enable sophisticated designs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a suite of services from design to selection of components, manufacturing, document and test a broad range of custom interconnect products. Our differentiator, in this very competitive business, is engineering support. We provide years of technical and manufacturing engineering experience coupled with a passion for helping customers “get it right”.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Why ICS? In today’s world, sophisticated customers can demand high quality, 100% on-time deliveries, flexible inventory control programs, continuous improvement and very aggressive pricing. ICS has consistently proven it can meet each of those criteria and be very successful. To further strengthen our competitive position, we offer superb engineering assistance. We will make available years of engineering experience and expertise at every step of the product development cycle that is desired. Product design, component selection, testing procedures and fixture development are all areas we excel in. We can shorten your time to market, reduce engineering changes, and reduce your product development costs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Education:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school dipoma/GED is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in wire harness production, aerospace manufacturing, or a similar field is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of soldering, wire crimping and testing equipment is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have strong written and verbal communication skills, and be able to read, comprehend and create written and verbal instruction in English.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent collaboration skills, with the ability to work well both individually and in a team setting, are required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in all aspects of production to ensure financial and customer requirements are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate outstanding abilities in conflict resolution, leadership presence, and organizational management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop strategy to grow technically and manufacture harnesses with higher quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate ability to inspect and identify non-compliant products and processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop strategy to support team development and rate manufacturing environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle any material types issued to production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track project completion timelines to support on time delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure manufacturing tools and equipment function properly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create a safe work environment for production teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Other responsibilities, initiatives and ad-hoc projects as required.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Internal and External Relationships&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position will work closely with ICS&#39;s quality and engineering departments, along with other technicians.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Physical Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met to successfully perform the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functio

&lt;h2 style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Inside Sales &amp;nbsp;Representative&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FLSA Status:&lt;/strong&gt; Exempt&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department:&lt;/strong&gt; Inside Sales&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Chandler, AZ&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation:&lt;/strong&gt; $60,000 – $78,000 (Based on Experience)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Sales Applications Specialist is responsible for driving revenue growth by supporting customers with technically accurate quotes, solutions, and product recommendations for complex cable assembly and interconnect applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role sits at the intersection of sales and engineering, acting as a key liaison between customers and internal teams to ensure requirements are clearly understood, quoted accurately, and executed to specification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At C.E. Precision Assemblies, a Trexon Company, our products support critical aerospace and defense applications where precision, compliance, and reliability are non-negotiable. This role plays a vital part in translating customer requirements into manufacturable solutions while delivering a high level of responsiveness and technical confidence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is detail-oriented, mechanically inclined, and comfortable working with drawings, specifications, and cross-functional teams in a fast-paced manufacturing environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Sales &amp;amp; Quoting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review customer RFQs, drawings, and specifications to develop accurate and competitive quotes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interpret technical requirements and collaborate with engineering and production to ensure feasibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recommend product solutions, materials, and configurations based on customer needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support pricing strategy by understanding labor, materials, and manufacturing processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow up on quotes to drive conversion and revenue growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customer Engagement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a primary point of contact for assigned customers, providing both commercial and technical support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage inbound and outbound communications to identify needs and generate opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate lead times, order status, and technical clarifications clearly and proactively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strong customer relationships through responsiveness and problem-solving&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with engineering, quality, production, and purchasing teams to align on customer requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support resolution of technical questions, discrepancies, and quality concerns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all customer requirements are properly documented and communicated internally&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Continuous Improvement &amp;amp; Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build knowledge of cable assemblies, interconnect systems, and applicable industry standards (IPC/WHMA-A-620, J-STD-001, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to improve quoting accuracy, turnaround time, and customer experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in ongoing training to strengthen both technical and sales capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Administrative &amp;amp; Reporting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate records of quotes, orders, and customer interactions in CRM/ERP systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support reporting, forecasting, and pipeline tracking as needed&lt;/l

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;CRE Underwater Connectivity&lt;/span&gt;, delivering subsea connectivity, designs and manufactures a range of all-metal shell connectors, fibre optic products, strain terminations, penetrators and junction boxes for extremely heavy duty use and are trusted in the most rigorous underwater applications on the planet from splash zone to full ocean depth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Soldering and/or assembly of subsea electrical assemblies and components in accordance with job card.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow technical drawings, assembly instructions and parts list to manufacture assemblies in line with customer expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completing relevant production and testing documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completing necessary preventative maintenance of all assembly equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow manufacturing priority plan set by production management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing time to maximise output while maintaining quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complying with safe working practices, following risk assessments, safe systems of work and COSHH requirements within the work cell.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring barcode scanners are used to ensure accurate tracking of all jobs within production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Undertaking any other duties which are assigned to you by management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills (mandatory)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to detail and quality under pressure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organisation and time management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to comply to company procedures and policy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to understand manufacturing drawings/schematics and identify any incorrect or missing information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills (desirable)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wiring of subsea cable assemblies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wiring of subsea penetrators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manufacture of subsea connectors and bulkheads.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oil filled assemblies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Personal Attributes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Focussed on safely handling all chemicals and manufactured products in line with the associated safety guidance to industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self – starter, can prioritise workload to meet client’s requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible, adaptable approach to workload.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer an attractive compensation package for skilled and experienced Technicians!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Objectives / Scope&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To define, implement and maintain a business development strategy for the group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and deliver a sales pipeline to meet the business growth targets within defence, renewable and oil &amp;amp; gas markets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and grow existing client relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expand the client portfolio into new markets and regions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Main Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interface and manage the sales pipeline from enquiry through to purchase order placement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and progress enquiry/sales order activities to collate data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide marketing support and assist with business forecasting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Business reporting on sales enquiries, market performance and opportunities, potential leads, success factor for obtaining new business and monthly KPIs to Head of Sales&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Identification of immediate, medium and long term opportunities both within existing accounts and new business&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively network both on and offline to generate new business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend, manage and lead trade shows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain strong client relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate new clients and leads&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interface with sales team and international business partners, and follow up on any potential leads&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Presentation and demonstration of the company’s products and services including technical and support services to potential clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand the market and any gaps between our client’s needs and our competitors’ products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Win and close sales opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaise with the Internal Sales team and effectively hand over any orders. Ensure that all requirements are accurately recorded and acknowledged&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Achieve maximum conversion rates from quotations to orders, with adherence to the quotation follow up process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaise with the wider business to provide customers with accurate information and quotations appropriate to their applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Input customer information from calls, visits, mails-shots etc, onto company databases immediately it becomes available&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate timely feedback on quotations with regular customer visits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Qualify the technical and environmental requirements for the customer application&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sales performance reporting to the group&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with training and job or product awareness for other staff within the company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain Group management behaviors practices and equal opportunity policy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comply with any environmental responsibilities as identified by the Group and communicated by your line manager that are relevant within your department&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Any other appropriate tasks that may be required to support the wider business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills base and experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent interpersonal communication and telephone manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to quickly develop an understanding of the group products and capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Target driven and results focussed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relevant business development experience, and a strong background within the industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree educated preferable but relevant experience will be considered as a suitable equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Connector/cables sales is highly desirable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Intelliconnect is a leading manufacturer of coaxial RF connectors, adaptors, and cable assemblies, supplying products to market sectors such as Aerospace &amp;amp; Defence, Medical, Industrial and Cryogenics. Intelliconnect is a rapidly growing business with an ambitious plan for future growth and investment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To ensure the timely, correct and cost efficient provision of materials for manufacturing, re-sale and non-production items. Ensuring that OnTime Delivery to Customers is maintained.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;GCSE English &amp;amp; Maths required. Relevant Degree / CIPS desirable.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3 years of experience in material planning and purchasing.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Knowledge&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of Purchasing techniques and proven track record of cost savings and process improvement.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good organisational skills.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use of MS Office Applications.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Procurement of components and finished goods in a timely, cost effective and correct manner.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Procurement of &#39;non-production&#39; materials, equipment, machinery and consumables in a timely, cost-effective manner.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sourcing new suppliers as desirable or necessary.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, implementation and maintenance of Vendor Management Programme,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaising with Production Manager to ensure efficient provision of materials and provide correct delivery times to customers and delivery information to Sales.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and report on activities and provide relevant management information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain purchasing databases/ERP parameters to ensure efficient material flow.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a safe working environment which complies with all aspects of the company H&amp;amp;S policies.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fully support companies SC21 activities and objectives.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Any other reasonable activity as requested by line manager.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is responsible for supporting the purchasing and procurement process by creating and issuing purchase orders for materials, parts, and services, tracking deliveries, and coordinating with suppliers to ensure timely fulfillment. The Buyer will monitor open orders, confirm lead times, follow up on late shipments, and escalate supply issues to help prevent production delays and reduce disruptions. This role works closely with internal teams such as production, engineering, and quality to align purchasing needs and maintain accurate procurement records in the ERP (Epicor) system. Success in this role requires strong attention to detail, organization, professional communication, and a willingness to learn procurement fundamentals in a fast-paced manufacturing environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma or GED required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Associate’s degree or Bachelor’s degree preferred (Business, Supply Chain, Operations, or related field)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;0–3 years of experience in purchasing, supply chain, manufacturing, or administrative support preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in a manufacturing environment preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Electronics component purchasing experience strongly preferred (ex: connectors, cable assemblies, wire, harness components)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Knowledge:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic understanding of purchasing, logistics, or manufacturing environments preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with purchase orders, invoices, and vendor communication is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Microsoft Excel and Outlook&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to prioritize multiple tasks and meet deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work cross-functionally with internal teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with an ERP system (Epicor) is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purchase Order Processing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and issue purchase orders for materials, parts, and services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure PO details are accurate (pricing, part numbers, quantities, ship-to, due dates)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain purchasing documentation and records in the ERP system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support invoice matching and resolution of PO discrepancies when needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Supplier Coordination &amp;amp; Follow-Up&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate with suppliers to confirm orders and lead times&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track open orders and follow up on late or at-risk deliveries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Escalate supply issues to the Procurement/Supply Chain Manager as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with supplier onboarding paperwork and updates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with production and planning teams to support material availability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with engineering and quality teams for supplier or part changes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with reporting related to spend, supplier performance, and open PO status&lt;/li&gt;
